## When to use
Use this skill when you need to monitor your disk usage more efficiently and want quick access to detailed disk status information.

## Approach
To enhance the functionality of a custom shell function for quick disk status, integrate `shell_exec` with commands such as `df -hT` and `du -sh /path/to/directory`. Additionally, add checks for filesystem errors using `fsck -n`.

## Example
```bash
disk_status() {
  local DISK_INFO=$(shell_exec "df -hT")
  local DU_INFO=$(shell_exec "du -sh /")
  local FSCK_INFO=$(shell_exec "fsck -n /dev/sda1 | grep 'Free blocks'")

  echo "$DISK_INFO"
  echo "$DU_INFO"
  echo "$FSCK_INFO"
}
```

## Pitfalls
- Ensure the `disk_status` function runs under sufficient permissions to access filesystem information.
- Be cautious about the path passed to `du -sh /path/to/directory`, as incorrect paths may yield unexpected results.